  "prompt": "What is the best pre workout drink before a long run?",
  "response": "Here are some good pre-workout drink options for a long run:\n\n1. Water\n- Always the most important basic hydration\n- Helps prevent dehydration during exercise\n\n2. Sports drinks with electrolytes\n- Gatorade, Powerade\n- Replaces electrolytes and provides quick energy\n- Good for runs over 60-90 minutes\n\n3. Beetroot juice\n- Natural performance enhancer\n- Improves oxygen flow and endurance\n- Can help reduce muscle fatigue\n\n4. Caffeine-containing drinks\n- Coffee or energy drinks\n- Boosts alertness and performance\n- Should be consumed 30-60 minutes before running\n\n5. Coconut water\n- Natural electrolyte source\n- Low in calories\n- Good for hydration\n\n6. Homemade smoothies\n- Blend of fruits, protein, and carbohydrates\n- Provides sustained energy\n- Examples: banana, berries, yogurt, honey\n\nTips:\n- Drink 16-20 oz of fluid 2-3 hours before running\n- Avoid heavy, high-fat drinks\n- Experiment to find what works best for your body\n- Stay hydrated throughout your run\n\nConsult a nutritionist or sports dietitian for personalized advice.",
